02:38.224 --> 02:39.858
<i>Hello.</i>

02:39.860 --> 02:41.527
This is Thomas Lang.

02:41.529 --> 02:43.462
<i>Hi. Are you...
Are you in Rome?</i>

02:43.464 --> 02:45.230
- Yes.
<i>- Oh, great.</i>

02:45.665 --> 02:47.266
<i>We should meet.</i>

02:47.268 --> 02:49.001
Okay. Where?

02:49.003 --> 02:51.303
<i>Um, we could meet
at Cafe Rosati.</i>

02:51.305 --> 02:52.985
<i>- It's near your hotel.</i>
- Uh-huh.

02:53.606 --> 02:55.340
<i>I'll be carrying
a copy of your book.</i>

03:00.446 --> 03:01.847
Good likeness?

03:02.815 --> 03:03.882
Not bad.

03:04.551 --> 03:06.084
- I'm Thomas.
- Hi. Simone.

03:06.086 --> 03:07.486
<i>Good to meet you.</i>

03:10.190 --> 03:12.090
- Have you lived here long?
- Fifteen years.

03:12.992 --> 03:15.627
<i>Grazie.</i> This is home now.

03:15.629 --> 03:17.863
It's not enough money for
foreign press bureaus, so...

03:17.865 --> 03:23.068
I cover, um,
Italy for <i> Newsweek,</i>
<i>Daily Beast,</i> CNN, BBC.

03:23.070 --> 03:25.103
- You must be good.
- I do okay.

03:25.738 --> 03:26.939
You've got family here?

03:26.941 --> 03:29.007
Yeah. Two young boys.

03:29.475 --> 03:30.542
And a husband.

03:32.779 --> 03:34.379
I was sent your book.

03:34.381 --> 03:35.981
Thought I was going to hate it.

03:35.983 --> 03:38.116
True crime isn't really
my thing.

03:38.118 --> 03:40.085
I was flying to New York
on the red-eye,

03:40.087 --> 03:42.554
couldn't sleep, so I read
your book instead.

03:42.556 --> 03:44.122
Take that as a compliment.

03:44.124 --> 03:45.857
Like it says on the cover,

03:45.859 --> 03:47.019
"Every parent's nightmare."

03:48.061 --> 03:49.962
- You have children?
- Daughter.

03:50.863 --> 03:52.231
I'm separated from her mother.

03:53.333 --> 03:54.533
I know.

03:55.501 --> 03:56.635
How old's your daughter?

03:57.637 --> 04:00.205
- She's nine.
- And what's her name?

04:00.207 --> 04:02.174
Bea. We call her Bea.

04:03.109 --> 04:04.776
Short for Beatrice.

04:04.778 --> 04:06.311
She was conceived in Italy.

04:06.313 --> 04:08.193
Her mom was acting
in a film here.

04:09.048 --> 04:10.349
It's a nice name.

04:10.917 --> 04:11.984
Yes.

04:13.186 --> 04:15.153
So, tomorrow's the end
of the appeal.

04:15.155 --> 04:17.189
Yes, round two begins.

04:17.190 --> 04:18.457
We'll need to leave
really early.

04:18.459 --> 04:19.858
Can you be at my apartment
by 7:00?

04:19.860 --> 04:21.360
Sure.

04:21.362 --> 04:23.195
But one piece of advice.

04:23.197 --> 04:25.864
If you're going to make
the film, make it a fiction.

04:25.866 --> 04:28.600
You can't tell the truth,
unless you make it a fiction.

04:28.602 --> 04:31.770
There are so many things
I couldn't put in my book
even though they were true.

04:31.772 --> 04:32.838
Okay.

04:51.024 --> 04:53.392
<i>In September, 2007,</i>

04:53.394 --> 04:56.828
<i>two young women arrived at
the university town of Siena.</i>

04:56.830 --> 04:58.497
<i>They were looking forward
with excitement</i>

04:58.499 --> 05:00.579
<i>to spending a year as
a student in Italy.</i>

05:01.367 --> 05:03.235
<i>Elizabeth Pryce and
Jessica Fuller,</i>

05:03.237 --> 05:05.070
<i>both rented rooms in this house,</i>

05:05.072 --> 05:07.606
<i>on the edge
of the medieval town.</i>

05:07.608 --> 05:10.275
<i>Two months later,
Elizabeth was dead,</i>

05:10.277 --> 05:12.644
<i>and Jessica had been accused
of her murder,</i>

05:12.646 --> 05:14.846
<i>along with her boyfriend,
Carlo Elias.</i>

05:16.015 --> 05:18.183
<i>The case made headlines
around the world,</i>

05:18.185 --> 05:19.685
<i>and the focus of attention</i>

05:19.687 --> 05:22.454
<i>was the character of
Jessica Fuller.</i>

05:22.456 --> 05:24.022
<i>Was she the cunning manipulator</i>

05:24.024 --> 05:25.691
<i>described by the prosecution?</i>

05:28.996 --> 05:31.163
<i>The quirky student
described by her mother...</i>

05:31.165 --> 05:33.365
She's smart. She's artistic.

05:33.367 --> 05:35.067
She's imaginative.

05:35.069 --> 05:39.604
<i>...or "Jessica Rabbit,"</i>
<i>as described</i>
<i>by the British media.</i>

05:39.606 --> 05:41.740
<i>A sexy, drug-taking
student killer.</i>

05:44.177 --> 05:47.112
<i>On Halloween, Jessica
was working in Bar Rumba,</i>

05:47.114 --> 05:49.014
<i>while Elizabeth partied
late into the night</i>

05:49.016 --> 05:50.248
<i>with some English friends.</i>

05:52.018 --> 05:54.519
<i>Elizabeth spent the next day
recovering.</i>

05:54.521 --> 05:58.123
<i>The last time she was
seen alive was 8:45 p.m.</i>

06:00.326 --> 06:03.695
<i>No one knows exactly
what happened after that.</i>

06:03.697 --> 06:05.597
<i>The only thing known for certain</i>

06:05.599 --> 06:08.467
<i>is Elizabeth died a brutal
and horrible death.</i>

06:11.971 --> 06:13.405
<i>One year later,</i>

06:13.407 --> 06:16.141
<i>the families
of Elizabeth and Jessica</i>

06:16.143 --> 06:19.044
<i>- were in court
to hear the verdict.</i>

06:33.526 --> 06:35.927
<i>Hello.</i>

06:36.863 --> 06:39.297
<i>Who's there?</i>
Is Bea there?

06:39.299 --> 06:41.466
- This is Thomas.
<i>- Who is it?</i>

06:41.468 --> 06:44.002
- Thomas, we...
- No. Bea is out with her mum.

06:45.405 --> 06:46.671
Okay. Then I'll try again
tomorrow.

06:46.673 --> 06:48.353
- Okay, bye.
- Yeah. Bye.

06:51.043 --> 06:52.544
You must know this road well.

06:52.546 --> 06:54.579
Yeah, every week for a year.

06:54.581 --> 06:57.382
Up to Siena on Thursday
and back on Saturday.

06:57.384 --> 07:00.819
Crazy Italian legal system
totally fucked up our lives.

07:00.821 --> 07:02.821
You were covering
this story from the beginning?

07:02.823 --> 07:04.256
Yeah. Pretty much.

07:04.258 --> 07:06.858
I was due to go to Modena
to test drive a Maserati,

07:06.860 --> 07:09.094
when ANSA,
the Italian wire service,

07:09.096 --> 07:11.897
said that an English student
had been murdered in Siena.

07:11.899 --> 07:14.166
<i>Well, I decided to
go take a look.</i>

07:14.168 --> 07:15.834
<i>I knew an Italian
journalist based there</i>

07:15.836 --> 07:18.703
<i>for</i> Corriere Della Sera,
<i>Roberto Feluci.</i>

07:21.541 --> 07:23.141
<i>Look, it's Maria Argento,</i>

07:23.810 --> 07:25.610
<i>head of the local homicide.</i>

07:25.612 --> 07:28.346
That's Polizia,
not Carabinieri?

07:28.348 --> 07:31.349
I know.
Carabinieri are furious.

07:31.351 --> 07:34.986
We're getting bits and pieces
of information, but we do know
that the victim's name

07:34.988 --> 07:36.555
is Elizabeth Pryce.

07:39.625 --> 07:41.460
She was found dead
in the bedroom

07:41.462 --> 07:44.062
<i>of her house that you can see
just behind me down there.</i>

07:55.141 --> 07:57.943
Worst part is, I bumped
into them later that day.

07:57.945 --> 07:59.411
I'm tired.

08:01.481 --> 08:04.583
Hi. Excuse me, I'm
a journalist from <i> Newsweek.</i>

08:04.585 --> 08:06.184
You were Elizabeth's roommate,
right?

08:06.186 --> 08:07.586
That's right.

08:07.588 --> 08:10.155
- Oh, it must be terrible.
- It's really shocking.

08:10.157 --> 08:12.858
I'm too scared to go back
in the house.

08:12.860 --> 08:14.292
I think I put in my notes, uh,

08:14.294 --> 08:16.394
"She's a dud.
He looks boring."

08:16.396 --> 08:18.363
I could've had a scoop.

08:18.365 --> 08:22.200
A world exclusive,
instead I left Siena to go
test drive the Maserati.

08:22.202 --> 08:24.202
- The one that got away.
- Exactly.

08:24.204 --> 08:25.837
I was still in Modena
when I heard that

08:25.839 --> 08:28.640
an American woman,
an Italian man and
a Congolese man

08:28.642 --> 08:31.576
<i>So, I turned around,
went straight back.</i>

08:32.311 --> 08:33.745
Hi, can I talk to you?

08:33.746 --> 08:35.480
Have you spoken
to your daughter?

08:35.482 --> 08:39.551
<i>At this point,</i>
<i>none of us knew</i>
<i>the names of the arrested.</i>

08:39.553 --> 08:40.652
Hey there.

08:40.654 --> 08:42.187
Okay,
listen up, everybody.

08:42.188 --> 08:45.223
In the, uh, Elizabeth Pryce
memorial sweepstake,

08:45.225 --> 08:46.625
the runners and riders are

08:46.627 --> 08:49.561
Jessica Fuller, Carlo Elias,

08:49.563 --> 08:51.963
- and, uh, Cedric Bapupa.
How do you know
this stuff?

08:51.965 --> 08:53.198
Sometimes you got to
leave the cafe, mate.

08:53.200 --> 08:54.266
- Even in the rain.
- Okay. Got it.

08:54.268 --> 08:57.235
Jessica Fuller, 21,
from Baltimore.

08:57.237 --> 09:00.539
Carlo Elias, 25.
Likes knives.

09:00.541 --> 09:02.941
- It's like a public confession.
- Yeah, or a suicide note.

09:02.943 --> 09:04.142
Who's Cedric Bapupa?

09:04.144 --> 09:06.545
He runs the bar where
Jessica works. Bar Rumba.

09:06.547 --> 09:08.179
I get scuppered
even in my own town.

09:08.181 --> 09:09.548
Yes, you do.
You get scuppered.

09:09.550 --> 09:12.083
Well, I see your meat-cleaver,
I raise you a gun.

09:12.085 --> 09:13.752
And a YouTube link.

09:13.754 --> 09:15.186
She's pretty.

09:15.188 --> 09:16.922
<i>You put this on YouTube,
you motherfucker,</i>

09:16.924 --> 09:19.124
<i>I'm going to kill you, okay?</i>

09:19.126 --> 09:20.358
<i>Now, they were unlucky.</i>

09:20.360 --> 09:22.060
The families tried to
erase the Internet info,

09:22.062 --> 09:23.361
but it was too late.

09:23.363 --> 09:25.897
All their dirty laundry
was hung out to dry.

09:38.711 --> 09:40.946
Thomas just wanted to meet,
and um,

09:40.948 --> 09:42.708
get your take on what happened.

09:44.183 --> 09:45.817
Of course.

09:45.819 --> 09:47.919
I'm asked many times.

09:47.921 --> 09:50.322
- When did you hear
about the killing?
- A phone call.

09:50.324 --> 09:51.990
<i>There wasn't much information.</i>

09:51.992 --> 09:53.391
<i>Just the address of the house.</i>

09:57.663 --> 10:00.165
<i>The burglary was false.</i>

10:00.167 --> 10:03.234
<i>Glass on top
of the disturbed clothing,</i>

10:03.236 --> 10:04.502
<i>wrong way around.</i>

10:05.471 --> 10:08.206
Most importantly, the body.

10:08.208 --> 10:10.075
<i>It was covered by a duvet.</i>

10:11.043 --> 10:13.278
At that moment,
I could feel it.

10:13.946 --> 10:15.080
Only a woman

10:15.082 --> 10:17.782
would cover a body
when it is already dead.

10:17.784 --> 10:19.651
The following day,
I asked Jessica

10:19.653 --> 10:21.620
to show me around the apartment.

10:22.555 --> 10:23.822
She was very calm.

10:23.824 --> 10:25.056
Very collected.

10:25.058 --> 10:26.591
When we came to the kitchen,

10:26.593 --> 10:28.460
I asked her
to look in the drawer

10:28.462 --> 10:31.363
and tell me if there were
any knives missing.

10:33.199 --> 10:34.833
She became hysterical.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.801
That is when we started to tap

10:36.803 --> 10:38.603
the phones of Jessica and Carlo.

10:44.210 --> 10:46.244
<i>We knew Carlo was lying.</i>

10:46.246 --> 10:49.948
He switched off his
phone at 8:45 that night.

10:50.383 --> 10:51.683
So had Jessica.

10:51.685 --> 10:54.986
They turned their phones on at
6:00 the next morning.

10:54.988 --> 10:56.921
He had no phone call
from his father.

11:04.797 --> 11:06.564
We checked his computer.

11:06.566 --> 11:08.466
He hadn't even surfed the net.

11:08.468 --> 11:11.236
They hadn't thought
through their alibis.

11:20.980 --> 11:23.615
Carlo and I went
back to his apartment.

11:23.617 --> 11:25.350
We watched a DVD together.

11:26.218 --> 11:27.819
<i>Amelie.</i>

11:27.821 --> 11:29.387
And then we had dinner.

11:29.389 --> 11:31.356
Together?
- Yes.

11:33.092 --> 11:34.559
Then we made love.

11:38.364 --> 11:41.499
You got a message on
your phone from Cedric Bapupa.

11:42.201 --> 11:44.135
You replied...

11:44.137 --> 11:46.004
- Did you see him?
- No.

11:46.006 --> 11:48.239
Why did you say
<i>"Ci vediamo pui tardi"?</i>

11:48.241 --> 11:49.874
I was just being friendly.

11:50.876 --> 11:52.377
If they were guilty,

11:52.379 --> 11:54.379
wouldn't they have worked out
what to say?

11:54.381 --> 11:57.515
People do not behave
rationally in cases like this.

11:57.517 --> 11:59.384
So she panicked
and accused Bapupa?

11:59.719 --> 12:01.319
Exactly.

12:01.321 --> 12:05.156
I met Cedric and took him back
to our house

12:05.158 --> 12:07.325
because he liked Elizabeth

12:07.327 --> 12:09.894
and wanted to start
something with her.

12:09.896 --> 12:12.397
Cedric and her
were in Lizzie's bedroom

12:12.399 --> 12:14.666
while I must've stayed
in the kitchen.

12:14.668 --> 12:17.502
At a certain point,
I heard Lizzie screaming.

12:19.004 --> 12:21.339
I was frightened of him.

12:21.341 --> 12:23.975
I got scared and put my hands
over my ears.

12:25.411 --> 12:27.879
I can't remember anything else.

12:42.628 --> 12:44.796
And why would she accuse
someone who's innocent?

12:44.798 --> 12:46.064
Who knows?

12:46.066 --> 12:49.267
Maybe she knew a black guy
had been involved somehow,

12:49.269 --> 12:50.769
thought, uh,

12:50.771 --> 12:52.771
accusing a different black man

12:53.606 --> 12:54.939
might confuse us.

13:51.263 --> 13:53.398
- Hey, darling.
- Joey.

13:54.900 --> 13:57.001
Joe, this is, um, Thomas.

13:57.003 --> 14:01.172
- Currently head of...
- Uh, this week the <i> Daily Mail</i> and Sky.

14:01.174 --> 14:02.807
- Oh, so, are you the film guy?
- Right.

14:02.809 --> 14:04.909
Who's gonna play me?
I bet everyone asks you that.

14:04.911 --> 14:06.644
- No, you're the first.
- Oh, great. Well, hey...

14:06.646 --> 14:09.047
- I'm thinking Colin Farrell.
- He's Irish.

14:09.049 --> 14:11.516
- Yeah. He's also really
good-looking, sensitive.
- This is perfect.

14:11.518 --> 14:13.585
Change the accent
and keep the face.

14:13.587 --> 14:15.153
- I'll bear him in mind.
- Sure.

14:15.155 --> 14:18.156
Listen. I love your wife's
TV show, by the way.

14:18.158 --> 14:20.358
She's not my wife.
She's my ex-partner.

14:20.360 --> 14:22.660
Yeah. It must have been very
difficult when you separated.

14:22.662 --> 14:24.229
Especially because
she moved in with her

14:24.231 --> 14:25.396
onscreen husband.

14:25.398 --> 14:27.098
Now, would you be interested
in talking about that?

14:27.100 --> 14:29.200
We could put across
your point of view, you know.

14:29.202 --> 14:30.635
The difficulty of having
your private life

14:30.637 --> 14:32.737
- picked over by
the gossip industry
- No. I wouldn't.

14:33.305 --> 14:34.405
It's worth a try.

14:34.407 --> 14:36.474
- Uh, are going to eat later?
- Sure.

14:36.476 --> 14:38.042
- Usual place? Uh-huh
- Yes.

14:38.911 --> 14:40.011
Sorry.

14:41.146 --> 14:42.546
- Hey. Hi.
- Hi.

14:47.686 --> 14:49.787
Hey. Hi, Bea.
<i>Hey!</i>

14:50.656 --> 14:52.490
- How are you?
<i>- Good.</i>

14:53.092 --> 14:54.158
<i>Where are you?</i>

14:54.593 --> 14:55.660
In Italy.

14:56.428 --> 14:58.129
<i>When are you coming home?</i>

14:58.597 --> 14:59.931
Uh, London home?

15:00.633 --> 15:03.134
<i>No. Your home. Here home.</i>

15:03.136 --> 15:05.403
Um, soon.

15:05.971 --> 15:07.572
- In a few weeks.
<i>- Okay.</i>

15:08.040 --> 15:09.340
I Miss you!

15:10.042 --> 15:12.911
Missing you, too.

15:12.913 --> 15:15.546
What you're up to?
<i>Bea, come on,</i>
<i>we're going to be late.</i>

15:15.548 --> 15:17.215
<i>Okay, coming!</i>

15:17.217 --> 15:18.683
<i>Well, I got to go, Daddy.</i>

15:18.685 --> 15:20.485
Okay.
I call you tomorrow, okay?

15:21.754 --> 15:22.887
Bea?

15:23.289 --> 15:24.355
Bea?

15:29.028 --> 15:30.895
- Hey.
- Hi, Sarah.

15:30.897 --> 15:32.664
- How are you?
- Good.

15:32.666 --> 15:34.265
- This is Sarah.
- Red or white?

15:34.267 --> 15:36.000
She's a producer
for the US networks.

15:36.002 --> 15:38.336
She has a special fondness
for Siena.

15:38.338 --> 15:41.639
Not. I spent so much
time here, my marriage
went down the pan.

15:41.641 --> 15:44.409
Just another casualty
of war reporting.

15:44.411 --> 15:46.811
- It's not really a war though.
- No, it kind of feels
like it though.

15:46.813 --> 15:48.513
There's all this competitive
flag-waving.

15:48.515 --> 15:50.114
It's like they're innocent
or they're guilty,

15:50.116 --> 15:51.349
and you can't be neutral.

15:51.351 --> 15:52.417
What do you think?

15:52.419 --> 15:53.685
I work for the networks.

15:53.687 --> 15:55.520
We pay for Jessica's
family to be here.

15:55.522 --> 15:58.122
So, they have spent
an absolute fortune

15:58.124 --> 16:00.224
on the flights, hotels,
lawyers,

16:00.226 --> 16:02.393
and we get exclusive
interviews in return.

16:02.395 --> 16:04.729
So she's innocent?

16:04.731 --> 16:06.998
Of course she is innocent.

16:07.000 --> 16:08.700
No, look, they have the guy
banged up.

16:08.702 --> 16:09.867
- Joseph, okay?
- Wrong guy.

16:09.869 --> 16:11.869
He had a criminal record.

16:11.871 --> 16:13.271
He had threatened
somebody with a knife.

16:13.273 --> 16:15.373
Right. So why did they
accuse Cedric Bapupa?

16:15.375 --> 16:16.641
Uh, why did they
switch the phone off?

16:16.643 --> 16:18.242
Why did she say she was
there and heard screams?

16:18.244 --> 16:19.544
And why sign a confession?

16:19.546 --> 16:21.412
And, uh, the blond hair
that they found on the body.

16:21.414 --> 16:22.480
Which they lost.

16:22.482 --> 16:23.915
When the police showed up
at the house,

16:23.917 --> 16:25.583
she and Carlo had
a mop and bucket.

16:25.585 --> 16:28.319
They'd been out at 7:00
in the morning buying bleach.

16:28.321 --> 16:29.487
What were they cleaning up?

16:29.489 --> 16:31.609
Why was she doing yoga
in the police waiting room?

16:34.661 --> 16:36.894
Listen. The police
and the prosecutors,

16:36.896 --> 16:39.964
they condemned the wrong
people in the wrong order.

16:39.966 --> 16:41.933
- And the press all
piled in after.
- That's what we do.

16:41.935 --> 16:44.102
At the end of the day,
she said she was there,

16:44.104 --> 16:46.637
in the house, on the night.
Guilty!

16:46.639 --> 16:48.373
- Game Over.
- Exactly.

16:48.375 --> 16:50.775
Why would they do it?
What's the motive?

16:50.777 --> 16:53.244
- You need a reason.
- Right. It's not a film.

16:53.246 --> 16:55.680
Okay? It's not
a Miss Marple mystery.

16:55.682 --> 16:58.216
Why does no one ever want to
make a story about Carlo?

16:59.819 --> 17:01.686
No. No.
Carlo is the quiet one.

17:01.688 --> 17:03.588
What will happen tomorrow
with the appeal?

17:03.590 --> 17:06.590
Yeah, we'll get our pictures,
and then we'll go.

17:06.593 --> 17:08.126
This is just
a really good excuse

17:08.127 --> 17:09.761
to catch up on all the gossip.

17:10.864 --> 17:12.430
How's your husband?

17:12.432 --> 17:14.464
- The last I heard...
- Is he still chasing
small boys in Morocco, or...

17:14.467 --> 17:16.334
Fucking your wife, actually.

17:17.569 --> 17:18.703
Someone has to.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.648
Good evening.

17:35.788 --> 17:37.308
- Well.
- Well.

17:37.723 --> 17:39.524
I guess it's goodnight.

17:39.526 --> 17:40.691
Guess so.

18:20.499 --> 18:22.366
You okay?
You need a pass.

18:23.569 --> 18:24.635
Thank you.

18:37.850 --> 18:40.118
Wow, she changed her style.

18:40.120 --> 18:41.586
They're not going to
make the same mistake twice,

18:41.588 --> 18:42.687
are they?

18:44.022 --> 18:45.623
How're you feeling today,
Jessica?

18:46.625 --> 18:48.392
I'm going to call that demure.

18:58.837 --> 19:01.105
Simone, how did Jessica
strike you today?

19:01.107 --> 19:03.441
Her hair was darker
than it was the last
time we saw her.

19:03.443 --> 19:06.043
She was wearing a very
demure skirt.

19:06.045 --> 19:08.813
She seemed older,
more composed.

19:08.815 --> 19:10.581
Her Italian had
improved a lot.

19:10.583 --> 19:12.283
And what can we expect
next from the case?

19:12.285 --> 19:13.651
The case has been adjourned,

19:13.653 --> 19:16.654
but the appellate process
could take many months.

19:26.065 --> 19:27.131
Hey.

19:27.499 --> 19:28.566
Coffee.

19:29.801 --> 19:31.035
- Hey.
- Hey.

19:31.037 --> 19:32.470
So, does it all make sense?

19:32.472 --> 19:34.305
Not yet. Too many angles.

19:34.307 --> 19:37.275
Jessica is innocent.
That is your story.

19:37.277 --> 19:38.609
Uh, this is Francesco.

19:38.611 --> 19:39.944
He's Joseph's lawyer.

19:39.946 --> 19:42.146
This is Thomas. He's making
a film about Jessica.

19:42.148 --> 19:43.714
Not about Jessica,
about the case.

19:43.716 --> 19:47.351
Hmm. You should make Joseph
your protagonist.

19:47.353 --> 19:49.220
His is the best story of all,

19:49.222 --> 19:51.022
and it tells you a lot
about Italy.

19:51.024 --> 19:52.223
Well, about the world.

19:52.225 --> 19:53.858
Go on.

19:53.860 --> 19:56.027
The police knew there was
someone else in the flat.

19:56.029 --> 19:58.763
Someone had a shit in
the toilet, and left it there.

19:58.765 --> 20:00.765
So they arrested Cedric Bapupa.

20:00.767 --> 20:04.302
Then he got lucky.
He got a cast-iron alibi.

20:04.304 --> 20:07.171
So the police start checking
their database.

20:07.173 --> 20:10.274
They found that the shit
belonged to Joseph Derma.

20:10.276 --> 20:13.978
A young guy who had been
adopted by a family in Siena.

20:13.980 --> 20:15.179
He was definitely involved?

20:15.181 --> 20:16.380
He was definitely
in the apartment,

20:16.382 --> 20:18.182
uh, we don't dispute that.

20:18.850 --> 20:19.917
A couple of days later,

20:19.919 --> 20:21.953
Joseph went to Munich.
He left Siena.

20:21.955 --> 20:24.422
The police got a friend
to contact him on Skype.

20:42.107 --> 20:44.008
So you see?
Jessica had nothing
to do with it.

20:44.010 --> 20:45.676
It was perfect for the police.

20:45.678 --> 20:47.678
They just swapped one
black man for another.

20:47.680 --> 20:49.714
Oh, come on,
you know he's guilty.

20:49.716 --> 20:51.148
There's no point playing
the race card.

20:51.150 --> 20:53.117
Joseph went
for a separate trial.

20:53.119 --> 20:54.185
I believe what he said.

20:54.187 --> 20:57.121
And he was the only one
who seemed genuinely sad

20:57.123 --> 20:58.256
by Elizabeth's death.

23:35.614 --> 23:38.048
Thomas, lovely, lovely,
lovely to meet you finally.

23:38.050 --> 23:40.084
- Hey. Adam. Nice to meet you.
- Hi.

23:40.086 --> 23:42.319
- Hi. How are you doing?
- Hi.

23:42.321 --> 23:45.189
So, we are all
very excited about this.

23:45.191 --> 23:48.292
We're absolutely thrilled
that you're on board.

23:48.294 --> 23:50.227
Well done, Steve, for dragging
him back from Hollywood.

23:50.229 --> 23:51.529
- Pleasure.
- This will be the first time

23:51.531 --> 23:53.264
that you guys have
worked together...

23:53.266 --> 23:55.466
Uh, since, uh, the last time.

23:56.536 --> 23:58.002
So, um,
what happened with your

23:58.004 --> 24:00.237
CIA in Central America project?

24:00.239 --> 24:01.639
First I got the stars
and no money,

24:01.641 --> 24:03.174
and then I got the money,
but lost the stars.

24:03.176 --> 24:05.376
Ah, such a shame.
I loved that script.

24:06.344 --> 24:08.612
Thomas, tell us, how was...
How was Italy?

24:08.614 --> 24:11.182
- Interesting.
- This is a great, great story.

24:11.184 --> 24:14.218
- It's gonna be wonderful.
- Siena is beautiful.
It's an amazing city.

24:14.220 --> 24:16.454
Should almost be
a character in the film.

24:16.456 --> 24:17.688
We have a clash of cultures,

24:17.690 --> 24:19.356
American, Italian, British...

24:19.358 --> 24:22.126
And two great parts
for young women.
Do you have any thoughts?

24:22.128 --> 24:24.495
Fortunately,
we are now blessed
with a whole

24:24.497 --> 24:26.363
ream of fantastic
young actresses.

24:26.365 --> 24:27.465
Carey Mulligan would be good.

24:27.467 --> 24:29.667
Yeah. She's very beautiful
in her acting...

24:29.669 --> 24:31.368
Well. I think I have to
work out the story

24:31.370 --> 24:32.736
before we start casting.

24:33.472 --> 24:34.772
- Yeah.
- Yep.

24:34.774 --> 24:37.508
Have you worked out what
your angle is going to be?

24:37.510 --> 24:41.545
I was thinking maybe
Simone herself. A journalist.

24:41.547 --> 24:43.427
Might be the right way
into the story.

24:43.949 --> 24:45.182
What's she like?

24:45.184 --> 24:47.952
Interesting. Intelligent.
Attractive.

24:47.954 --> 24:50.154
- How old is she?
- Mid-30s.

24:50.156 --> 24:53.424
I think that a whole world
of foreign correspondence
could be rich for us.

24:53.426 --> 24:54.492
Sort of an exile.

24:54.494 --> 24:57.194
- Naomi Watts?
- Chloe Sevigny maybe?

24:57.196 --> 24:58.462
Or Tina Fey?

24:58.464 --> 25:00.431
I love Tina Fey. She's...

25:00.433 --> 25:03.534
They just need a sense
of how you see the story.

25:04.469 --> 25:06.370
Sure. Okay.

25:06.372 --> 25:09.406
You going to work
on the script here or in LA?

25:09.408 --> 25:10.608
- Here in Italy.
- Mmm-hmm.

25:10.610 --> 25:13.477
Not in LA. Can't concentrate.

25:13.479 --> 25:16.580
Everybody knows Katherine,
or knows someone
who knows Katherine

25:16.582 --> 25:18.616
from some fucking party
or other.

25:18.618 --> 25:21.519
And there's
all that shit with Timothy,
custody issues and...

25:23.389 --> 25:25.055
I hate this fucking prick.

25:26.157 --> 25:28.225
Did you really threaten
to kill him?

25:28.227 --> 25:31.495
It makes me sick to think
of Bea growing up with
him in that house.

25:32.531 --> 25:33.597
Another drink?

25:35.066 --> 25:36.834
- Can I get two more, please?
- Same again?

25:36.836 --> 25:38.196
Yeah, that'd be great,
thanks, man.

25:38.537 --> 25:39.603
Of course.

25:42.207 --> 25:44.708
I was thinking of flying back
to Italy for Halloween.

25:44.710 --> 25:46.443
Shoot some documentary stuff.

25:46.445 --> 25:47.678
Won't cost that much.

25:47.680 --> 25:50.381
Yeah, it's a good idea.
Go for it.

25:58.156 --> 25:59.657
Is it in focus?

25:59.659 --> 26:01.058
No, it's not in focus.

26:04.863 --> 26:06.497
Pan with her.

26:15.041 --> 26:16.273
Okay if we film you?

26:17.108 --> 26:19.310
Uh, yeah, sure.

26:19.312 --> 26:21.278
We should go back to
Piazza del Campo now.

26:21.280 --> 26:22.546
It'll be busier there.

26:22.548 --> 26:24.582
Well, you know what we need.
Go ahead, I'll catch up.

26:24.584 --> 26:25.649
- Okay.
- Yep.

26:25.651 --> 26:26.717
I got it. Here.

26:37.929 --> 26:38.996
Happy Halloween!

26:38.998 --> 26:41.031
- Can I get a drink?
- Yeah, of course.

26:42.067 --> 26:43.601
It's what I'm here for.

26:43.603 --> 26:46.070
We have a special
on zombies tonight.

26:46.072 --> 26:47.371
- Try one.
- Good, good.

26:47.373 --> 26:48.505
Where you from?

26:48.507 --> 26:49.807
Uh, I'm from London, actually.

26:49.809 --> 26:51.108
- Oh, really?
- Wandsworth.

26:51.110 --> 26:52.876
- Oh, wow. Know it.
- Really?

26:52.878 --> 26:55.613
- Yeah, I lived in London
for six years.
- Oh, no way!

26:55.615 --> 26:57.314
So, what are you filming?

26:57.316 --> 26:59.083
Did you hear about
the Jessica Fuller case?

26:59.085 --> 27:00.618
Yeah, 'course.

27:00.620 --> 27:01.952
Is it another documentary?

27:01.954 --> 27:03.387
- Film.
- Are you the director?

27:03.389 --> 27:05.189
- Yes, I am.
- No way.

27:05.191 --> 27:07.791
- Do you live in Siena?
- Uh, I've been here
about six months.

27:07.793 --> 27:09.326
It's lovely.

27:09.328 --> 27:11.295
Do you need any actresses,
by any chance?

27:11.297 --> 27:14.131
Um, no. Not yet. But a guide.

27:14.133 --> 27:15.899
I want to see the real Siena.

27:15.901 --> 27:17.801
Do you work here every night?

27:17.803 --> 27:20.237
Most nights, not always.

27:20.239 --> 27:22.640
I can give you my number,
if that helps?

27:23.208 --> 27:24.508
Yeah. Sure.

27:24.510 --> 27:25.576
Cool.

27:32.083 --> 27:33.183
Call me if you need me.

27:33.952 --> 27:35.786
Sure. What's your name?

27:35.788 --> 27:37.755
- Uh, I'm Melanie.
- Thomas.

27:37.757 --> 27:39.390
Nice to meet you, Thomas.

27:44.763 --> 27:46.363
- How are you?
- Good.

27:46.365 --> 27:48.165
Hey. How'd it go?

27:48.167 --> 27:50.868
Wasn't quite the Sodom
and Gomorrah your book
made it out to be.

27:50.870 --> 27:52.202
Oh, it's still early.

27:52.204 --> 27:54.304
You got to give the town
a chance.

27:54.306 --> 27:55.506
Did you get to the red zone?

27:55.508 --> 27:57.107
Uh-huh. The crew were only
booked until midnight.

27:57.109 --> 27:59.710
That doesn't go on
until 1:00 a.m.. So...

27:59.712 --> 28:01.612
Let's go anyway.

28:01.614 --> 28:03.374
I want to see Siena
at its worst.

28:10.955 --> 28:12.056
It's left here.

28:19.664 --> 28:20.898
Simone.

28:26.504 --> 28:27.871
What's the matter?

28:27.873 --> 28:30.941
Are you scared to see me
after what you wrote?

28:30.943 --> 28:32.242
- This is Thomas.
- Hello.

28:32.244 --> 28:33.510
I know who he is.

28:33.512 --> 28:35.412
You want to be careful
with this one.

28:35.414 --> 28:37.581
She seems so nice
when you meet her.

28:37.583 --> 28:41.118
Then, when she writes,
she turns into a real bitch.

28:41.120 --> 28:43.721
- Come and have a drink.
- We're on our way
to the red zone.

28:43.723 --> 28:45.355
Come on,
that's for shitty students.

28:45.357 --> 28:47.091
You're not students, are you?

28:47.093 --> 28:48.492
Not for a long time.

28:50.128 --> 28:53.230
In a murder, the dead body
tells you a lot.

28:53.232 --> 28:55.933
I saw Elizabeth's body,
in the morgue.

28:56.401 --> 28:57.568
How?

28:57.570 --> 28:58.836
I visit the morgue often.

28:59.237 --> 29:01.205
I have a cousin.

29:01.207 --> 29:03.440
It's important to look
death in the face

29:03.442 --> 29:05.709
if you want to understand life.

29:05.711 --> 29:08.479
That's why there are
so many murder stories.

29:08.481 --> 29:10.414
Every news program is
full of killings,

29:10.416 --> 29:12.015
so many films.

29:12.017 --> 29:14.151
Death is the end of
everyone's story.

29:15.453 --> 29:17.121
The only thing we share,

29:17.123 --> 29:19.003
now we no longer
believe in God.

29:22.460 --> 29:24.862
And so we have become
obsessed with killings.

29:25.997 --> 29:29.066
Real killings,
fictional killings...

29:29.068 --> 29:31.135
But from the safety
of our homes,

29:32.036 --> 29:33.270
where the only issue is,

29:34.172 --> 29:35.439
"Who done it?"

29:36.341 --> 29:38.408
Not what it means.

29:38.410 --> 29:40.511
When we see it on TV
and not in the flesh.

29:40.513 --> 29:42.780
In the flesh,
when a friend dies,

29:42.782 --> 29:44.915
we don't even want
to see the body.

29:45.650 --> 29:47.351
So what did the body tell you?

29:48.153 --> 29:49.953
That Jessica didn't do it.

29:49.955 --> 29:51.555
So why is she on trial?

29:52.457 --> 29:54.358
Police here are the worst.

29:54.360 --> 29:55.993
Corrupt, incompetent.

29:55.995 --> 29:57.715
Everyone is corrupt here, but...

29:58.429 --> 29:59.863
She didn't kill her.

30:00.498 --> 30:02.232
I know her. We have talked.

30:03.067 --> 30:04.401
She is intelligent.

30:05.904 --> 30:07.871
Not like most of
the students here.

30:07.873 --> 30:09.973
The students I teach are idiots.

30:09.975 --> 30:12.342
Not Jessica.
She has true understanding.

30:13.244 --> 30:15.212
So you think it was
one of the others?

30:15.214 --> 30:18.282
Carlo had a collection
of knives, okay?

30:18.284 --> 30:20.324
Elizabeth was killed
with more than one knife.

30:21.419 --> 30:23.153
But the police never found them.

30:23.155 --> 30:24.555
Because they are fools.

30:25.957 --> 30:27.191
I know where they are.

30:27.193 --> 30:29.560
So why don't you just give
them to the police, Edoardo?

30:30.795 --> 30:32.963
They will try to frame me.

30:32.965 --> 30:35.165
And they have already
arrested me before.

30:36.301 --> 30:38.168
They broke my finger.

30:38.170 --> 30:40.204
I would be an easy target,
like Cedric.

30:40.206 --> 30:42.172
- A scapegoat.
- Come on.

30:42.174 --> 30:44.708
No one likes me because
I write the truth.

30:44.710 --> 30:47.678
I tell the world
how stupid they are.

30:47.680 --> 30:49.560
Have you already
talked to Cedric?

30:51.082 --> 30:52.616
- No.
- Why?

30:53.585 --> 30:54.751
Are you hiding people from him,

30:54.753 --> 30:57.221
or don't you know
as much as you pretend?

30:57.223 --> 30:59.423
Cedric Bapupa is
a friend of mine.

30:59.425 --> 31:01.191
If you want to meet him,
I can set it up.

31:01.193 --> 31:02.993
Yeah, for a price.

31:02.995 --> 31:04.928
Always a price for everything.

31:04.930 --> 31:07.030
Do you think
you are the only one
allowed to make

31:07.032 --> 31:08.398
money from this story?

31:08.933 --> 31:10.000
Hmm?

31:10.002 --> 31:12.369
You're not a guy whose
life was ruined by it.

31:14.272 --> 31:15.606
Quite a character.

31:15.608 --> 31:17.074
Hmm, yeah.

31:17.076 --> 31:19.676
His blog had stuff on it
that nobody else knew.

31:19.678 --> 31:22.045
We all had to read it
every day to keep up to speed.

31:22.047 --> 31:24.615
He has the time
and he knows everybody,

31:24.617 --> 31:26.049
and he also has money.

31:26.051 --> 31:27.818
He rents out rooms
all over the city.

31:27.820 --> 31:29.152
Really cheap.

31:29.154 --> 31:30.487
Almost squats.

31:30.489 --> 31:33.223
And they say he deals
drugs on the side.

31:33.225 --> 31:35.158
- Handy man to know.
- -Yeah.

31:36.327 --> 31:38.762
Sometimes I think he might
actually be the killer.

31:38.764 --> 31:40.831
When we were
covering the trials,
somebody decided

31:40.833 --> 31:42.933
that Joe and I were
having an affair,

31:42.935 --> 31:45.969
and they put it
on the Internet.

31:45.971 --> 31:47.971
It was just an easy way
of attacking somebody who

31:47.973 --> 31:49.439
wasn't on Jessica's side,

31:50.275 --> 31:51.708
but I think it was Edoardo.

31:53.478 --> 31:57.814
It wasn't true,
but I had to tell my husband.

31:58.416 --> 31:59.549
Mmm.

32:00.852 --> 32:02.185
We're separated now.

32:20.805 --> 32:24.074
<i>"The man</i>
<i>who lies asleep</i>
<i>will never waken fame,</i>

32:24.076 --> 32:26.743
<i>"and his desire and
all his life drift past him</i>

32:26.745 --> 32:30.681
<i>"like a dream, and the traces
of his memory fade from time</i>

32:30.683 --> 32:33.684
<i>"like smoke in air
or ripples on a stream."</i>

32:37.422 --> 32:38.522
Hi.

32:38.524 --> 32:39.690
- Hey.
- Hey.

32:39.692 --> 32:41.224
This seat taken?

32:44.729 --> 32:47.664
- Pretty view.
- Yeah.

32:49.233 --> 32:54.271
What's this?
Oh, bit of light reading.

32:54.273 --> 32:57.107
Calls itself a comedy,
but not that many laughs.

32:57.109 --> 32:58.675
Are you in heaven or hell?

32:58.677 --> 32:59.910
Inferno.

33:02.013 --> 33:03.613
I have to go back to Rome.

33:03.615 --> 33:05.315
I have the kids this weekend.

33:05.317 --> 33:06.717
Lucky you.

33:10.021 --> 33:12.289
Okay, have a good one.

33:19.964 --> 33:21.565
- Bye.
- Bye.

34:20.525 --> 34:21.757
Hey. It's me, Thomas.

34:21.760 --> 34:22.926
<i>Hey, Thomas!</i>

34:22.928 --> 34:24.261
I'm in your bar,
but you're not here.

34:24.263 --> 34:27.097
<i>I'm at a party.
Not much of a party, but...</i>

34:27.099 --> 34:28.231
<i>Do you wanna come?</i>

34:28.233 --> 34:29.966
I thought it wasn't any good.

34:29.967 --> 34:33.003
<i>It's your typical
student party, so...</i>

34:33.005 --> 34:34.804
- Then I have to come.
<i>- Okay, great!</i>

34:34.806 --> 34:36.039
For research.

34:36.041 --> 34:37.107
<i>Good.</i>

34:41.012 --> 34:42.579
- Hey.
- Hey.

34:48.485 --> 34:50.120
Mr. Director.

34:51.190 --> 34:53.989
- You can call me Thomas.
- 'Course.

34:53.992 --> 34:55.672
So, this is
your comeback film.

34:57.027 --> 34:59.796
Hope so. How do you know?

34:59.798 --> 35:01.398
I looked you up on
<i>Siena's Burning.</i>

35:01.400 --> 35:03.533
- Do you know the blog?
- Yeah.

35:03.535 --> 35:05.902
Don't believe
everything you read.

35:05.904 --> 35:08.038
'Course.
Only the good things.

35:09.240 --> 35:11.108
Here it is. Come on.

35:27.425 --> 35:29.392
- This is Thomas.
- Hi.

35:32.763 --> 35:34.464
Thomas, everyone.
Everyone, Thomas.

35:34.466 --> 35:35.699
Hey.

35:39.904 --> 35:41.471
- Do you have a lighter?
- Yeah.

36:36.561 --> 36:37.661
Hey.

36:39.430 --> 36:40.964
What are you doing here?

36:42.266 --> 36:45.135
- Come with me.
- I'm tired.

36:45.137 --> 36:47.170
Come.

36:47.172 --> 36:49.906
How can you make a movie
about the murder if you

36:49.908 --> 36:53.109
haven't even seen where
the killing happened?

36:53.111 --> 36:55.845
- Listen, it's late.
- No time like the present.

36:55.847 --> 36:57.647
Strike while the iron's hot.

36:57.649 --> 37:00.016
Don't you know your
English sayings?

37:20.638 --> 37:22.505
This is the window they entered.

37:25.843 --> 37:28.144
Don't throw stones if
you live in glass houses.

37:41.859 --> 37:44.261
Come on, it's empty!

37:44.263 --> 37:47.931
If you were here that night,
you could have saved her.

37:49.233 --> 37:51.101
That's what everyone dreams.

37:54.839 --> 37:56.539
This is Elizabeth's room.

37:58.376 --> 38:00.410
She was found by the wardrobe.

38:02.446 --> 38:04.180
Look what they didn't find.

38:13.157 --> 38:16.192
This is the knife
that killed her.

38:16.194 --> 38:18.828
But the police never even
looked under the wardrobe.

38:20.231 --> 38:24.868
They didn't even look
under the fucking wardrobe.

38:48.059 --> 38:49.959
- You all right?
- Yeah.

38:50.761 --> 38:52.062
I'm sorry.

