54:40.645 --> 54:43.746
<i>It is four-something.</i>

54:43.748 --> 54:45.281
<i>What time is it there?</i>

54:45.283 --> 54:46.915
It's late, after midnight.

54:46.917 --> 54:49.251
<i>Oh, wow, that's pretty late.</i>

54:50.654 --> 54:52.087
<i>You must be really tired, huh?</i>

54:53.223 --> 54:54.290
I can't sleep.

54:56.092 --> 54:57.526
<i>Are you okay, Daddy?</i>

54:59.229 --> 55:00.629
Listen,

55:03.300 --> 55:04.780
I gotta call you tomorrow, okay?

55:05.068 --> 55:06.869
<i>Okay. Bye.</i>

55:07.237 --> 55:08.604
Bye.

55:32.195 --> 55:35.731
<i>No sadness is</i>
<i>greater than in misery to</i>
<i>rehearse memories of joy.</i>

55:47.678 --> 55:49.411
- Welcome back, Mr. Lang.
- Thank you.

55:50.080 --> 55:51.747
<i>How long are
you staying for?</i>

55:51.749 --> 55:52.815
<i>Not sure.</i>

56:06.196 --> 56:08.130
No, it's nice.
It's definitely nice.

56:10.534 --> 56:13.135
Um, I've gotta go.
See you later.

56:13.137 --> 56:14.577
- Bye.
- Bye, guys.

56:15.171 --> 56:16.611
- Hey.
- Hey.

56:17.674 --> 56:19.375
Strange, seeing you
in the daylight.

56:19.377 --> 56:21.276
Why, do I look different?

56:21.278 --> 56:23.679
- Even more beautiful.
- Thank you.

56:23.681 --> 56:25.521
I like a bit of
old-fashioned courtesy.

56:30.387 --> 56:32.020
Hey, Edoardo.

56:32.288 --> 56:33.622
Hi.

56:35.759 --> 56:37.659
My friend Thomas is
looking for a place to stay.

56:37.661 --> 56:40.596
I told him I knew
someone who could help.

56:40.598 --> 56:41.830
Sit down.

56:47.804 --> 56:49.684
I'm too old for
a student accommodation.

56:50.206 --> 56:51.373
Well, I have lots of places,

56:51.375 --> 56:52.875
and the best addresses.

56:52.877 --> 56:54.176
Really?

56:54.178 --> 56:56.218
Did Simone tell you
something different?

56:56.880 --> 56:58.781
Be careful with her.

56:58.783 --> 57:01.703
If you believe everything
she says, you will
never know the truth.

57:03.586 --> 57:05.087
Do you read my blog?

57:05.855 --> 57:07.222
No.

57:07.224 --> 57:10.859
You should.
I say some very kind
things about you.

57:11.761 --> 57:14.263
- Didn't I, Melanie?
- Yeah.

57:14.265 --> 57:16.432
- Do you wanna drink?
- No, thank you.

57:20.703 --> 57:22.771
This was my uncle's house.

57:22.773 --> 57:24.239
He was a doctor.

57:32.348 --> 57:34.308
This is a perfect
place for writing.

57:34.951 --> 57:36.185
Full of atmosphere.

57:37.520 --> 57:38.787
I'll take it.

57:39.722 --> 57:40.956
How much?

57:40.958 --> 57:43.058
Money, we will talk later.

57:43.060 --> 57:45.961
First, I want you
to read my script.

57:45.963 --> 57:50.466
I have been watching
your old movies,
and I like the naivete.

57:52.268 --> 57:55.637
I'm having a small
gathering of friends tonight.

57:55.639 --> 57:57.406
I'll come to
collect you, okay?

58:27.904 --> 58:33.175
<i>"Then I saw a serpent</i>
<i>with six feet dart forth</i>
<i>in front of a man.</i>

58:33.177 --> 58:36.478
<i>"With middle feet,</i>
<i>it bound him</i>
<i>'round the paunch,</i>

58:36.480 --> 58:39.715
<i>- "and, with the forward ones,
his arms it seized.</i>

58:46.189 --> 58:48.423
<i>"Already the two heads
had one become.</i>

59:58.061 --> 59:59.161
Come on, we are late.

01:00:00.096 --> 01:00:02.397
You know the way is hard.

01:00:02.399 --> 01:00:04.600
No one gets anywhere
by lying in bed.

01:00:05.468 --> 01:00:06.868
You have to work.

01:00:06.870 --> 01:00:08.670
Work even when
you don't know why.

01:00:09.238 --> 01:00:11.039
Where are we going?

01:00:11.041 --> 01:00:12.841
Where the thieves are.

01:00:13.142 --> 01:00:14.209
Oi.

01:00:16.679 --> 01:00:18.280
Thomas Lang.

01:00:37.767 --> 01:00:40.702
Yeah?
<i>Hey, Thomas.</i>
<i>Where are you?</i>

01:00:40.704 --> 01:00:42.337
I'm in... I'm in my flat.

01:00:52.315 --> 01:00:53.382
Hi.

01:00:53.384 --> 01:00:54.850
Hey.

01:00:54.852 --> 01:00:56.118
You good?

01:00:56.120 --> 01:00:57.319
Yeah.

01:01:00.556 --> 01:01:01.623
Where are we going?

01:01:01.625 --> 01:01:03.065
- To see Edoardo.
- Oh.

01:01:06.229 --> 01:01:09.331
I really think you should be
making a love story.

01:01:09.333 --> 01:01:11.733
All the best movies
are love stories.

01:01:11.735 --> 01:01:15.570
<i>Romeo and Juliet.
Casablanca. Annie Hall.</i>

01:01:15.572 --> 01:01:16.838
<i>Beauty and the Beast.</i>

01:01:18.908 --> 01:01:20.609
- Ciao.
- Hi.

01:01:25.248 --> 01:01:26.314
Hello, Thomas.

01:01:26.316 --> 01:01:27.416
Hey.

01:01:28.051 --> 01:01:29.151
What's the matter?

01:01:30.687 --> 01:01:32.988
Why you always seem so scared?

01:01:32.990 --> 01:01:34.990
What is it you're scared of?

01:01:34.992 --> 01:01:37.392
Maybe having to
make another movie.

01:01:37.394 --> 01:01:39.895
In case it's another failure.
Come on.

01:01:41.164 --> 01:01:43.098
Ignore him, it's all right.

01:01:48.771 --> 01:01:51.606
Don't worry, I know
the people who live here.

01:01:51.608 --> 01:01:53.909
- I own the house.
- I'll wait here.

01:01:54.510 --> 01:01:55.610
See you in a minute.

01:02:03.119 --> 01:02:06.855
The reason my
script is good is that
I know what happened.

01:02:06.857 --> 01:02:11.059
Art has to provide
the answer to the
questions that life asks.

01:02:11.061 --> 01:02:14.262
I know you don't agree
with me, but you are wrong.

01:02:14.264 --> 01:02:16.598
There is the truth,
and there is the rest.

01:02:17.734 --> 01:02:18.967
The killing happened here.

01:02:20.436 --> 01:02:21.503
I was watching there.

01:02:22.305 --> 01:02:23.872
I saw it with my own eyes.

01:02:23.874 --> 01:02:24.940
What happened?

01:02:27.009 --> 01:02:30.412
Joseph was in
love with Elizabeth.
He wanted her.

01:02:31.414 --> 01:02:32.534
But she didn't want him.

01:02:34.117 --> 01:02:35.317
So he killed her.

01:02:36.753 --> 01:02:37.819
Like <i> Othello.</i>

01:02:40.790 --> 01:02:43.024
Like this.

01:02:51.634 --> 01:02:53.468
Sorry it's so noisy.

01:02:53.470 --> 01:02:55.303
Come with me.

01:02:55.305 --> 01:02:56.772
See you in a bit.

01:02:56.774 --> 01:02:58.039
See you.

01:03:05.982 --> 01:03:09.351
I have decided,
you can read my script.

01:03:10.686 --> 01:03:12.354
But you can't
take it away with you.

01:03:12.356 --> 01:03:15.023
I don't trust anybody
with my story.

01:03:15.025 --> 01:03:16.925
You have one hour, that's all.

01:04:29.732 --> 01:04:31.199
- Hi.
- Hey.

01:04:31.201 --> 01:04:32.901
- Can I come in?
- Sure.

01:04:34.871 --> 01:04:36.171
You look terrible.

01:04:36.173 --> 01:04:37.305
Do I?

01:04:42.678 --> 01:04:44.412
Where did you go last night?

01:04:44.414 --> 01:04:46.214
I was getting worried about you.

01:04:46.716 --> 01:04:48.083
Edoardo freaked me out.

01:04:51.754 --> 01:04:52.988
It's so dark in here.

01:04:56.592 --> 01:04:57.859
No wonder you're depressed.

01:05:02.965 --> 01:05:04.032
That's better.

01:05:04.967 --> 01:05:06.967
I have something that
might cheer you up.

01:05:07.536 --> 01:05:08.703
You're gonna like it.

01:05:09.739 --> 01:05:11.406
<i>La Vita Nuova.</i>

01:05:12.275 --> 01:05:13.808
Thank you.

01:05:13.810 --> 01:05:16.645
Dante describes how he falls
in love with Beatrice.

01:05:16.647 --> 01:05:18.613
And then how she dies.

01:05:18.615 --> 01:05:20.715
For a moment,
he toys with the idea
of loving someone else,

01:05:20.717 --> 01:05:23.885
but he'll never love
anyone like Beatrice.

01:05:24.954 --> 01:05:26.821
It's so romantic.

01:05:26.823 --> 01:05:30.358
All those circles of hell
in The Divine Comedy,
it's boring.

01:05:30.360 --> 01:05:32.727
Everyone getting
punished for no reason?

01:05:32.729 --> 01:05:34.162
That is a book of love.

01:05:36.265 --> 01:05:38.667
Hopefully that will
make you happy.

01:05:38.669 --> 01:05:40.602
I'm late for class.
I've gotta go.
Are you gonna be okay?

01:05:40.604 --> 01:05:42.237
- Mmm-hmm.
- Promise?

01:05:42.239 --> 01:05:43.838
- Yeah.
- Good.

01:05:45.408 --> 01:05:47.128
I just want you to be happy.

01:05:50.112 --> 01:05:51.179
I'll see you later.

01:05:52.014 --> 01:05:53.081
Bye.

01:06:30.052 --> 01:06:32.454
<i>"It was exactly
the ninth hour of the day</i>

01:06:32.456 --> 01:06:34.456
<i>"when she gave me
her sweet greeting.</i>

01:06:35.658 --> 01:06:38.693
<i>"I was filled with such
joy that I had to withdraw</i>

01:06:38.695 --> 01:06:42.230
<i>"from the sight of others</i>
<i>and return to the</i>
<i>loneliness of my room.</i>

01:06:46.236 --> 01:06:47.602
<i>"As she walked
down the street,</i>

01:06:47.604 --> 01:06:49.804
<i>"she turned her eyes
towards me,</i>

01:06:49.806 --> 01:06:52.240
<i>"where I stood in fear
and trembling."</i>

01:07:36.352 --> 01:07:38.232
- I need your help.
- With the film?

01:07:39.155 --> 01:07:40.321
With Edoardo.

01:07:40.323 --> 01:07:41.956
Maybe you should
steer clear of him.

01:07:41.958 --> 01:07:44.325
Maybe you were right.
Maybe he was
involved in the killing.

01:07:44.327 --> 01:07:45.827
- Okay, stop.
- No, listen, listen, listen.

01:07:45.829 --> 01:07:47.362
I think he was there.
He took me to the house.

01:07:47.364 --> 01:07:48.596
He's got knives.
He saw the killing.

01:07:48.598 --> 01:07:50.131
He talks a bunch of shit,
he's messing with your head.

01:07:50.133 --> 01:07:51.399
No, I got to steal the knives.

01:07:51.401 --> 01:07:52.467
- I need you to help.
- No.

01:07:52.469 --> 01:07:55.603
I need you to get them
to Rome, to a lab,
test them for DNA.

01:07:55.605 --> 01:07:56.971
- No.
- I'll bring them to
you in the morning.

01:07:56.973 --> 01:07:58.339
Let go of me.

01:08:04.246 --> 01:08:05.613
Hello, Thomas.

01:08:05.615 --> 01:08:07.549
This is Thomas.
He's a director.

01:08:09.452 --> 01:08:11.453
I'm sorry I couldn't finish
your script last time.

01:08:11.455 --> 01:08:12.520
Yeah, why? You disappeared.

01:08:12.522 --> 01:08:13.822
I felt sick.

01:08:13.824 --> 01:08:15.523
Can I finish it?

01:08:16.492 --> 01:08:19.928
Okay.
You'll get another chance.

01:08:19.930 --> 01:08:22.363
But then you must tell me
that you want to make it.

01:08:33.375 --> 01:08:34.809
One hour, okay?

01:09:08.010 --> 01:09:09.077
Damn.

01:09:14.116 --> 01:09:15.183
Shit.

01:11:34.724 --> 01:11:35.957
Did you come to
my flat last night?

01:11:35.959 --> 01:11:37.025
Yeah, but you weren't there.

01:11:37.027 --> 01:11:38.747
Did you take the knives
from my bed?

01:11:39.194 --> 01:11:41.496
No. What... What knives?

01:11:41.498 --> 01:11:43.197
Thomas, Thomas!

01:11:43.699 --> 01:11:45.099
Thomas!

01:11:53.175 --> 01:11:54.642
What the fuck
are you doing here?

01:11:54.644 --> 01:11:57.145
I wanted to know
if you read my script.

01:11:57.147 --> 01:11:58.546
I didn't read your
fucking script.

01:11:58.548 --> 01:12:00.214
- Then you'll never
know what happened.
- Get out of here.

01:12:00.216 --> 01:12:02.050
Get out of here!

01:12:02.052 --> 01:12:04.085
Have you been
looking for this, hmm?

01:12:04.087 --> 01:12:06.321
Did you think you had
stumbled on the truth?

01:12:07.022 --> 01:12:08.523
You're an idiot.

01:12:08.525 --> 01:12:12.026
These are film props.
I photographed
them for my blog.

01:12:12.028 --> 01:12:14.729
And you should read it.
You wouldn't be so ignorant.

01:12:32.681 --> 01:12:34.615
- Where are the knives?
- Huh? What knife?

01:12:34.617 --> 01:12:36.484
Where are the real knives?

01:12:40.055 --> 01:12:41.522
Hey, hands off!

01:13:07.449 --> 01:13:09.717
You really have come off
the rails, haven't you?

01:13:13.389 --> 01:13:15.757
They're letting you go.
Let's get out of here.

01:13:18.260 --> 01:13:21.863
You're lucky. Edoardo's
not gonna press charges.

01:13:21.865 --> 01:13:23.825
Says you need a doctor,
not a prison cell.

01:13:26.402 --> 01:13:28.336
Looks like you hit him
pretty hard.

01:13:29.705 --> 01:13:30.905
Good.

01:13:32.408 --> 01:13:34.409
I'm going back
to Rome tomorrow.

01:13:34.411 --> 01:13:37.178
Stefano, Elizabeth's
boyfriend's willing to talk.

01:13:37.180 --> 01:13:38.513
It's his first interview.

01:13:39.214 --> 01:13:40.334
You should come with me.

01:13:40.649 --> 01:13:41.849
Yep.

01:13:41.851 --> 01:13:43.851
I have to get back to work.

01:13:43.853 --> 01:13:46.287
Get some rest
or something, okay?

01:13:46.289 --> 01:13:47.769
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

01:15:19.648 --> 01:15:22.049
<i>Have you written</i>
<i>anything yet?</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

01:15:22.051 --> 01:15:23.985
Really?

01:15:23.987 --> 01:15:25.620
Been thinking of
taking your advice.

01:15:25.622 --> 01:15:27.588
Making the film fictional.

01:15:27.590 --> 01:15:30.057
Setting it in Florence
as a tribute to Dante.

01:15:30.059 --> 01:15:32.026
Florence was the earthly
paradise he lost.

01:15:32.028 --> 01:15:35.830
Must be nice to have
had an earthly paradise,
even if you lose it.

01:15:37.266 --> 01:15:38.566
Right?

01:15:40.736 --> 01:15:45.873
I don't wanna make
a film about fear
or death or killing.

01:15:47.676 --> 01:15:49.516
I want to make
a film about love.

01:15:56.618 --> 01:15:58.853
<i>Yes?</i>

01:16:06.194 --> 01:16:08.996
I lived in the flat
below the girls.

01:16:08.998 --> 01:16:12.400
I met Elizabeth at the
beginning of the term.

01:16:12.402 --> 01:16:16.604
She came down in our flat
sometimes with Ana.

01:16:16.606 --> 01:16:20.007
We would hang out together,
smoke a little weed.

01:16:20.009 --> 01:16:23.077
Mmm. In court, it was
made very simple.

01:16:23.079 --> 01:16:27.982
That, um, Jessica was the
bad girl and Elizabeth
was the good girl.

01:16:27.984 --> 01:16:29.684
She was just normal.

01:16:29.686 --> 01:16:32.253
She liked parties.
She liked having fun.

01:16:32.888 --> 01:16:34.922
She like making love.

01:16:35.824 --> 01:16:37.725
She was beautiful.

01:16:37.727 --> 01:16:41.729
I didn't know her
for very long,
but I still think of her.

01:16:42.664 --> 01:16:44.365
I will always think of her.

01:17:04.686 --> 01:17:06.687
Ah, shit, I'm late.

01:17:06.689 --> 01:17:08.322
I'm gonna have to pick up
the kids on the way, okay?

01:17:08.324 --> 01:17:09.523
Sure.

01:17:20.268 --> 01:17:22.203
Hey, you guys,
I'm sorry I'm late.

01:17:22.205 --> 01:17:24.472
- Again?
- The traffic was really bad.

01:17:24.474 --> 01:17:27.408
- Andrew, Will. This is Thomas.
- Hey.

01:17:27.410 --> 01:17:29.310
- How was your day? Good?
- Good.

01:17:29.312 --> 01:17:31.178
Yeah? What did you do?

01:17:31.780 --> 01:17:33.180
Nothing much.

01:17:41.623 --> 01:17:43.958
- Your taxi's here.
- Thanks for looking after me.

01:17:44.559 --> 01:17:46.360
No problem.

01:17:46.362 --> 01:17:47.828
Bye.

01:17:49.931 --> 01:17:51.532
You talk to Katherine recently?

01:17:51.534 --> 01:17:52.600
No.

01:17:52.602 --> 01:17:55.436
You should.
Bea is yours and hers.

01:17:56.038 --> 01:17:57.705
That's how it is.

01:17:58.607 --> 01:18:00.047
- Bye.
- Bye.

01:18:01.276 --> 01:18:02.343
Take care.

01:18:10.886 --> 01:18:13.988
<i>Exterior. Siena. Night.</i>

01:18:13.990 --> 01:18:15.790
<i>The sounds of students partying</i>

01:18:15.792 --> 01:18:18.392
<i>drifts up from
the streets below.</i>

01:18:18.394 --> 01:18:21.429
<i>Elizabeth hangs out with
her boyfriend, Stefano.</i>

01:18:21.431 --> 01:18:24.632
<i>Sometimes Jessica
and Carlo are there.</i>

01:18:24.634 --> 01:18:27.968
<i>They smoke weed, drink beers,
go to parties.</i>

01:18:27.970 --> 01:18:29.670
<i>They're typical students.</i>

01:18:32.140 --> 01:18:34.875
<i>Elizabeth loves art,
music, literature.</i>

01:18:36.411 --> 01:18:39.580
<i>She visits the cathedral,
the galleries, the libraries.</i>

01:18:40.682 --> 01:18:43.484
<i>Siena is everything
she hoped it would be.</i>

01:18:43.486 --> 01:18:44.885
<i>She's happy.</i>

01:18:44.887 --> 01:18:47.321
<i>Looking forward
to the year ahead.</i>

01:19:04.372 --> 01:19:06.640
Back into the
belly of the beast.

01:19:06.642 --> 01:19:08.482
Yeah, let's try
and avoid that.

01:19:09.244 --> 01:19:11.746
I booked you
a room in the hotel.

01:19:11.748 --> 01:19:14.014
- Keep you in the real world.
- Thanks.

01:19:19.020 --> 01:19:20.387
Heads up, verdict's at 8:00.

01:19:21.189 --> 01:19:23.390
- Hey.
- -Okay.

01:20:43.205 --> 01:20:46.340
We are thankful that Jessica's
nightmare is finally over,

01:20:47.075 --> 01:20:49.210
and we'd like to
thank the court

01:20:49.845 --> 01:20:51.946
for searching for the truth,

01:20:51.948 --> 01:20:55.082
<i>and for overturning
this conviction.</i>

01:21:21.509 --> 01:21:23.077
Justice has been done.

01:21:23.079 --> 01:21:25.579
They are right
to release Jessica.

01:21:25.581 --> 01:21:29.750
Uh, one young life had
been already tragically taken.

01:21:30.552 --> 01:21:32.052
Why take another two?

01:21:32.054 --> 01:21:33.621
Based on what?

01:21:33.623 --> 01:21:37.024
Assumption by the police
and the self-interest
of the press.

01:21:38.059 --> 01:21:40.394
- Thank you.
- -Okay.

01:21:49.804 --> 01:21:54.174
Our daughter Elizabeth
has been completely forgotten.

01:21:54.176 --> 01:21:56.944
It's... It's very hard to
find any forgiveness.

01:21:58.513 --> 01:22:00.748
We know that four years
is a long time, but, um...

01:22:03.652 --> 01:22:05.219
Yeah, it's still very raw.

01:22:15.063 --> 01:22:16.530
Hey.

01:22:16.532 --> 01:22:18.132
<i>- Hi, Dad.</i>
- Hi.

01:22:18.867 --> 01:22:20.367
How are you?

01:22:20.369 --> 01:22:21.635
<i>Good.</i>

01:22:22.370 --> 01:22:23.437
<i>How are you?</i>

01:22:23.439 --> 01:22:24.538
I'm good.

01:22:25.807 --> 01:22:27.441
<i>Is the case over?</i>

01:22:27.909 --> 01:22:29.443
Yeah, it is.

01:22:30.979 --> 01:22:32.913
<i>What happened?</i>

01:22:32.915 --> 01:22:34.581
They say they were innocent.

